parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS (Supplemental Restraint System) can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: the airbag warning light is on
the airbags fail to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
occupants suffer injuries or fatalities due to lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Occupant Position Detection System (OPDS) unit can lead to the malfunction of the SRS system, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: the airbag warning light is on
the OPDS unit needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission synchronizers can cause the gears to grind or pop out, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift into incorrect gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues can cause faulty lights, buzzing sounds, and other malfunctions, which can distract the driver and increase the risk of accidents.
